headline: High-Yield Kraft Heinz Stock Was a Big Letdown in 2024. Could 2025 Be Any Better?
summary: The biggest attraction of Kraft Heinz (NASDAQ: KHC) as 2025 gets underway is most likely its lofty 5.2% dividend yield.  The average consumer staples company is yielding just 2.5%, less than half as much.  Here's what you need to know if you are looking at Kraft Heinz as Wall Street enters a new year.
